Signed and dated MD (L?) XVIII; Collection: Charles I; Literature: 37th volume of the Walpole Society 1958-60; Abraham van Doort's Catalogue of the Collection of Charles I. Edtied with a introduction by Oliver Millar, pp. 69 (N°.36) and 225; Mentioned in van der Doort's ""Register"" of the royal Collection completed in 1639 [...] N° 36 in the list of pictures in ""the King's Chare rooms in the privy Gallery"" and is described: Done by ye young Brugill, Given to the King by [...] In the original Ashmolean manuscript of the Register, a working draft from which fair copies were later made, a note is added, ""Given to the king by Mr. Endimoin Porter o. 8 -o. 7."" The manuscript in the Victoria and Albert Museum, a catalogue of the king's pictures compiled in 1640 probably by Sir James Palmer record [...]; [blad 2] A drummer and a ffluter done by old Peter Brewgill [...]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[2 bladen] [blad 1] PIETER BRUEGEL THE ELDER (c. 1528-1569); A SOLDIER PLAYING A FIFE, ANOTHER A DRUM AND A THIRD RAISING A BANNER. Signed and dated MD (L?) XVIII; Collection: Charles I; Literature: 37th volume of the Walpole Society 1958-60; Abraham van Doort's Catalogue of the Collection of Charles I. Edtied with a introduction by Oliver Millar, pp. 69 (N°.36) and 225; Mentioned in van der Doort's ""Register"" of the royal Collection completed in 1639 [...] N° 36 in the list of pictures in ""the King's Chare rooms in the privy Gallery"" and is described: Done by ye young Brugill, Given to the King by [...] In the original Ashmolean manuscript of the Register, a working draft from which fair copies were later made, a note is added, ""Given to the king by Mr. Endimoin Porter o. 8 -o. 7."" The manuscript in the Victoria and Albert Museum, a catalogue of the king's pictures compiled in 1640 probably by Sir James Palmer record [...]; [blad 2] A drummer and a ffluter done by old Peter Brewgill [...]</content>
